Usage: sh makeBAM.sh <pbam> <ref> <tmp> <prompt> <diff>

input: <pbam>, name of the pbam file; make sure the diff file has the same name and is in the same folder
<ref>: reference genome or transcriptome with path 
<tmp>: name of the tmp folder (will be automatically deleted)
<run_type>: options: genome is for genome aligned pbams, transcriptome is for transcriptome alined pbams
<diff> is the .diff filename
output: <bam>, a bam file that has the same name as pbam and diff (with a bam extension)
